       Sometimes processes, typically those  in  the  background,
       are  printed  with  null  or garbaged arguments.  In these
       cases, the name of the command is printed in  parentheses.

       w  does not know about the conventions for detecting back-
       ground jobs.  It will  sometimes  find  a  background  job
       instead of the right one.

       Unlike  other BSD versions of this command, the load aver-
       ages are not computed or displayed.

